🎯 Mentor's Advice

When troubleshooting network problems, follow this order instead of guessing:

Is the network interface up? (ip link)
Does the server have an IP address? (ip a)
Is the route correct? (ip route)
Can it reach another IP? (ping 8.8.8.8)
Does DNS work? (nslookup or dig)
Is the service listening? (ss -tulpn)
Can the application respond? (curl)
What do the logs say? (journalctl)

This systematic process is exactly how experienced DevOps engineers diagnose networking issues in production.

